          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWoTmzRVts4wRa9elxLXtfsIowinrxH5zfxMhtDrD-LBZz6-B7R=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I'm laughing while I write this, but YES, this is probably New York City's nicest & cleanest public park restrooms (Translation for UK visitors: WC, toilet) (Translation for Canadians: washrooms). There were two orderly lines (one for men, the other for ladies) and a reasonably short wait. With fresh cut flowers, constantly cleaned & well-maintained facilities, and at least two attendants, this is the bathroom you have to visit. Reminder: Don't forget to tip the attendant(s) - though it's optional.",
