        {
          "username": "Suresh Jayaraman",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "103492512530111117672",
          "user_review_count": 329,
          "user_photo_count": 5989,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGYKtE4G056gHrANSZ_K0R63NUjGt-aN4fTLdCBGrQwIXhefKzcw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "By far the best and cleanest public restroom in NYC Manhattan Midtown area. Toilets are cleaned perodically by 2 to 3 attentends every 15 to 20 mins. The queue is well managed by couple of staff as well. The western toilets also have themselves plastic wrapped for added cleanliness. That's the best part as even the private bathroooms on cleanest high-end 5 star hotels on this area doesn't have one like that. Trust me when I say this as I have stayed in most hotels on this area as a frequent visitor to NYC. Fresh flowers on the entrance, amazing music and the artwork of the building or amazing.\n\nLocated just above 5th Ave Bryant Park Station. B,D,F,M and 7 trains will take you there. Just 50 m walk from subway. Most of the times there is a queue for both men and women. So be ready to wait upto 10-15 mins before you can go in. Every individual need to wait I queue no matter how urgent you need to go in. You may get lucky on some rainy day but most of the times you gotta wait.!!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQydmFyZ1RnEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x1ad0cbfaf4a93b53!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgID2vargTg%7C%7C?hl=en",
